== About
From autumn 2021 I'm a Computer Science Master's student at the University of St. Gallen. My interests include core CS topics, as well as applications of Computer Science in Economy / Finance, Biology, Mathematics and Physics. 

Recently, I became particularly intererested in Quantum Computing and it's applications in Optimisation, Finance and Chemistry. I'm also interested in the development of promising of ideas into enterprises. I am strong proponent for more entrepreneurial engagement in Europe, as it is a centre of scientific innovation, but commercialization often happens outside of Europe.

Also, I like spending time on my bike, in my running shoes, on the water or playing the violin (I'm inclined to both classical music and art).


